-- 
Kamor Motors Soars to Highest Level on Record on Delek Talks

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-07-10T15:09:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-10/kamor-motors-soars-most-in-four-years-on-delek-automotive-talks.html
Kamor Motors Ltd. (KMRS) , an importer of
BMW vehicles to Israel, surged to the highest level on record
after its controlling shareholders said they were in talks to
sell their stakes based on a value of 245 million shekels ($72
million).  The shares climbed 31 percent, the most since November 2006
when Bloomberg began tracking the stock, to 16.40 shekels at the
4:30 p.m. close in Tel Aviv, giving the company a market value
of 207.5 million shekels.  Kamor Ltd., which owns about 64 percent, and two owners
with a combined 19.5 percent stake are in talks to sell their
shares to  Delek Automotive Systems Ltd. (DLEA) , according to a
 statement to the Tel Aviv Stock Exchange  today.  Kamor Ltd. (KMOR)  rose 5.1 percent to 9.461 shekels, the highest
level since May 2010. Delek Automotive gained 3.6 percent to
37.98 shekels, the most since July 3.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susan Lerner in Jerusalem at 
